attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt malware families. It contains specialized scanner modules targeting vulnerabilities in Realtek (UPnP/picsdesc.xml), Zyxel (ViewLog.asp), and Huawei (DeviceUpgrade_1) devices, alongside a Telnet brute-forcing module with hardcoded credentials. The sample includes several DDoS attack vectors (SYN, UDP, and STD floods) and establishes a command-and-control (C2) connection to 104.168.101.27. It also features a 'killer' module to eliminate competing malware processes and uses process renaming (prctl) to evade detection. The presence of the string 'Resentual Got You!' further indicates its malicious intent.
